- Min Heap : 
- At top : smallest milegaa 
- It tells whoever we visit till now , whose max and min
- get top : 1
- insertion : log n ( consider that tree ) 
- deletion : log n 

- Max Heap : 
- At top : largest milegaa 
- get top : 1
- insertion : log n ( consider that tree ) 
- deletion : log n 

// Max Heap : 
priority_queue <int> pq;

// Min Heap : 
priority_queue <int,vector<int>,greater<int>> pq;

// Basic operations 
push : pq.push(n);
pop : pq.pop();
top : pq.top();
empty : pq.empty();
size : pq.size();

// Pattern Recognise 
- Top k 
- kth smallest largest
- closest forthest 
- min max of every step
- merge sorted arrays ( 2+ arrays )
- stream of data
- rearrangement while keeping best ( pyramid ) 
